            "The evaluators had varying levels of emphasis on the need for results to discuss the specific emission line diagnostic methods used in the main paper."
        ],
        "key_insights": [
            "Claude highlighted the importance of results discussing the limitations and biases of different AGN selection methods.",
            "Gemini emphasized the need to prioritize results that investigate AGN in low-mass or dwarf galaxies using emission line diagnostics, particularly He II.",
            "DeepSeek noted the value of results that validate AGN candidates using multiwavelength data and address potential contaminants like ULXs."
        ],
        "suggested_focus": [
            "Discuss the trade-offs between prioritizing results that use the same diagnostic methods as the main paper (BPT, He II) versus considering alternative methods that could provide complementary insights.",
            "Determine the appropriate balance between results that focus exclusively on low-mass/dwarf galaxies and those that address AGN activity in a broader context.",
            "Explore strategies to effectively incorporate multiwavelength data and address potential biases or contaminants in AGN selection."
